                        <div class="people-card-grid-modal-right">
                            <h3>Jeremy Tasch</h3>
                            <h5></h5>
                            <p class="bio">Dr. Jeremy Tasch is a geographer specializing in, broadly conceived, political ecologies and resource geopolitics. He applies his thematic interests regionally in Central Eurasia, Russia-in-Asia, the circumpolar north, and is exploring newer research in Serbia. He has been a Fulbright scholar in Azerbaijan, the Kyrgyz Republic, the Russian Far East, and served as the Fulbright Distinguished Chair in Sustainable Development in Moscow, Russia.  Dr. Tasch holds a BA in Geography and Cartography, and Russian Studies, Temple University; an MS in Energy Management and Policy, the University of Pennsylvania; and a Ph.D. in Geography, Clark University.  His service as MAD’s Councilor runs through 2026.</p>
